We may compare the Ode with the Epistle (1. 10) addressed to the same Fuscus, the motto of which may be said to be‘ Fuge magna? v. 32. ‘A harmless, pious life is the true secret of safety and of happiness '-the Ode dresses this doctrine in the garb of poetry and religion— the Epistle in that of philosophy and worldly wisdom.
